@mjmmoh202018 Dark matter is a theoretical form of matter which is thought to be creating the gravitational pull required for maintaining a galactic structure. There isn't enough visible matter in a galaxy that would produce enough gravitation to form a galaxy, but there's clearly some extra gravity since galaxies continue existing anyway, and the source of that extra gravity is thought to be dark matter. Dark energy on the other hand, is the theoretical repulsive force that pushes celestial bodies away from each other and therefore expanding the universe.
